enums.name: LifecycleStage

values.name: Active
values.doc: The metric is included in experiment analysis.

values.name: Inactive
values.doc: The metric is excluded from experiment analysis but remains available for future use.

enums.doc: Lifecycle stages of an experiment metric, determining whether the metric is included in experiment analysis.

enums.name: DesiredDirection

values.name: Increase
values.doc: An increase to the metric value is desired. E.g., Success rate, Total revenue.

values.name: Decrease
values.doc: A decrease to the metric value is desired. E.g., Error rate, Latency.

values.name: Neutral
values.doc: Neither an increase nor a decrease to the metric value is desired, or the desired direction depends on other factors. E.g., Number of video play attempts, Number of user feedbacks

enums.doc: Desired direction for an experiment metric value.

enums.name: ExperimentMetricType

values.name: EventCount
values.doc: Counts the occurrences of an event. Experiment analysis accounts for unequal traffic allocation.

values.name: UserCount
values.doc: Counts the number of unique users who encounter an event. Experiment analysis accounts for unequal traffic allocation.

values.name: EventRate
values.doc: Calculates the percentage of events that satisfy a specified condition.

values.name: UserRate
values.doc: Calculates the percentage of users who encounter a start event and subsequently encounter an end event. Users must encounter the start event before the end event to be counted.

values.name: Sum
values.doc: Calculates the sum of a specified event property. Experiment analysis accounts for unequal traffic allocation.

values.name: Average
values.doc: Calculates the average value of a specified event property.

values.name: Percentile
values.doc: Calculates a specified percentile of an event property.

enums.doc: How the metric definition calculates metric values from event data.

values.name: FailedSchemaValidation
values.doc: The metric definition does not conform to the required schema.

values.name: UnsupportedEventCondition
values.doc: The filter condition is valid but not currently supported.

values.name: InvalidExperimentMetricDefinition
values.doc:
The provided metric definition is invalid.
For example, defining a metric to calculate the average of a numeric property but
including a filter condition that compares it to a string value creates a type mismatch.

enums.name: Versions

values.name: 2025-05-31-preview
values.doc: The 2025-05-31-preview version of the Azure Online Experimentation service.

The percentage of users who saw an advertisement for a subscription promotion and then later successfully subscribed. This metric is calculated as the number of users who successfully subscribed after seeing the advert divided by the total number of users who saw the advert. Users who saw multiple adverts or subscribed multiple times are counted only once. Users who saw the advert before the analysis period starts are excluded from this metric.
